This paper is primarily focused on image enhancement using neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of mobile phone hardware and efficient network architectures, which could also fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning models, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of mean opinion score (MOS) as a metric for evaluating image quality, which could fall under graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
